We recommended that the procuring entity strictly adhere to the pertinent provisions of the 2016 Revised Implementing Rules and Regulations to ensure transparency and accountability in the procurement process. We specifically recommended that:
The Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) comply with the posting requirement to ensure timely dissemination of the procurement opportunity;
The BAC invite in writing three (3) observers in all stages of the procurement activities to sits in its proceedings and ensure that the invitation is received within the prescribed period;
The BAC adopt the required procedures and conditions in the Post-Qualification stage particularly in the verification, validation and ascertainment of all statements made and documents submitted by the bidder with the Lowest Calculated Bid to ensure that they are in accordance with the requirements as stated in the Bidding Documents;
The BAC, though its Secretariat, see to it that the Notice of Award, Notice to Proceed and a copy of the approved contract were posted in the PhilGEPS website within three (3) and fifteen (15) calendar days from their respective issuances for information purposes; and
The Municipal Engineering Office integrate the Construction Safety and Health Program (CSHP) in the computation of project’s construction cost of all projects to be implemented to ensure the protection and welfare of the public within the vicinity of the worksite.

